    explanation: "The severity of a segregation-of-duties deficiency depends on whether compensating controls adequately mitigate the risk. If management reviews all purchases above a threshold, independently reconciles vendor statements, and reviews budget-to-actual variances, the compensating controls may reduce the risk that a material misstatement would go undetected, keeping this at a significant deficiency rather than a material weakness.",
