    explanation: "Government Auditing Standards (GAGAS / \"Yellow Book\"): Issued by the Comptroller General/GAO. Apply to: audits of government entities, entities receiving government funds, and programs/activities involving government funds. Key differences from GAAS: (1) Additional requirements for auditor independence (conceptual framework approach + specific prohibitions), (2) CPE requirements (80 hours per 2-year period, 24 hours in government auditing), (3) Report on internal control and compliance (required, even in a financial statement audit), (4) Peer review requirements.",
