    explanation: "AU-C 505.08 through 09 provides guidance when management refuses confirmation requests: (1) inquire about the reasons for the refusal and evaluate their reasonableness; (2) consider the implications for the assessment of fraud risk (management's refusal may indicate a risk of misstatement or fraud); (3) determine whether alternative procedures can provide sufficient appropriate evidence (e.g., subsequent receipts, shipping records, other documents); (4) if alternative procedures cannot provide sufficient evidence, evaluate the effect on the auditor's opinion (scope limitation potentially leading to qualification or disclaimer). An unreasonable refusal should heighten the auditor's professional skepticism and may trigger reconsideration of fraud risk.",
