    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "A search for unrecorded liabilities is designed to test the completeness assertion for payables. Common procedures include: (1) examining cash disbursements made after year-end — payments for goods/services received before year-end should have been accrued; (2) examining unmatched receiving reports — goods received before year-end without a corresponding recorded payable indicate an omission; (3) reviewing vendor invoices received after year-end for goods/services provided before year-end; (4) inspecting purchase orders and contracts for obligations at year-end; (5) inquiring of management about unpaid bills, accruals, and commitments. This procedure uses the source-to-records direction of testing (starting from reality, tracing to the books).",
