      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - AU-C 240 specifically requires auditors to evaluate significant unusual transactions, especially those outside the normal course of business, to identify potential fraudulent financial reporting. This evaluation includes assessing the business rationale and ensuring appropriate accounting treatment to detect management override.",
