    explanation: "AU-C 230.15 requires the auditor to assemble the final audit file on a timely basis, no later than 60 days after the report release date (the documentation completion date). During this 60-day period, the auditor may: (1) assemble and organize workpapers; (2) add administrative items (cross-references, sign-off sheets); (3) delete superseded drafts. After the 60-day period, the auditor should not delete or discard existing documentation. Additions after the documentation completion date must be documented with the date, by whom, and the reasons. For PCAOB engagements (issuers), the period is 45 days. The assembled file should be retained for the applicable retention period (generally 5 years for non-issuers, 7 years for issuers).",
