      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - ASC 842 requires a comprehensive audit approach encompassing proper lease identification, classification (finance vs. operating), accurate measurement of the right-of-use asset and lease liability, and complete disclosures to ensure fair presentation.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Focusing solely on total lease expense overlooks the balance sheet impact of leases, specifically the right-of-use asset and lease liability, which are key components of ASC 842.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - ASC 842 applies to all leases, regardless of their term length, with limited exceptions for short-term leases (12 months or less).",
