    educational: "ASC 842 significantly changed lease accounting, bringing most leases onto the balance sheet. Auditors must now assess not only the income statement impact (lease expense) but also the balance sheet impact (right-of-use asset and lease liability). Understanding the five classification criteria (transfer of ownership, purchase option, lease term major part of asset life, present value of payments substantially all of asset's fair value, specialized asset) is crucial.",
    examTip: "On the exam, remember that ASC 842 requires a holistic view of leases, impacting both the income statement and balance sheet; don't get tricked by options that focus on only one aspect.",
