      2: "Why option C is WRONG - While fee arrangements can impact independence, focusing solely on the timing of fee payments ignores other crucial areas like financial interests and relationships.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - New client acceptance procedures are important for risk management but are distinct from the ongoing independence policies needed to maintain objectivity with existing clients.",
