    educational: "The Sarbanes-Oxley Act (SOX) aims to protect investors by enhancing the reliability and accuracy of corporate financial statements. A key component of SOX is maintaining auditor independence, which is achieved by restricting the types of non-audit services that auditors can provide to their public company audit clients. This prevents auditors from auditing their own work or having conflicts of interest.",
    examTip: "When answering SOX questions, focus on the underlying principle of auditor independence; if a service creates a potential conflict of interest or self-review threat, it's likely prohibited.",
    memoryAid: "Remember 'BAM LIME' - Bookkeeping, Appraisal, Management, Legal, Internal Audit, MIS, Expert. These are the main prohibited services.",
    reference: "SOX §201; SEC Rule 2-01",
