      2: "Why option C is WRONG - CAMs, by definition, relate to accounts or disclosures that are material to the financial statements. Immaterial items, no matter how interesting, are not CAMs.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - CAMs are external communications within the auditor's report, not internal firm communications. Internal communications are part of the audit documentation but not CAMs.",
