      2: "Why option C is CORRECT - The COSO framework defines five integrated components of internal control: Control Environment, Risk Assessment, Control Activities, Information and Communication, and Monitoring Activities. These components work together to provide reasonable assurance regarding the achievement of an entity's objectives.",
