      1: "Option B is WRONG because an audit provides reasonable, not absolute, assurance that the financial statements are free from material misstatement. Auditors are not guarantors of fraud detection.",
      2: "Option C is WRONG because while the fee is an important part of the engagement, the engagement letter must also include details about the scope, responsibilities, and reporting framework to be compliant with auditing standards.",
