    explanation: "AU-C §250 (Laws and Regulations): Two categories: (1) Laws with a direct and material effect on financial statement amounts (e.g., tax laws, pension laws) — auditor must obtain evidence of compliance, (2) Other laws — auditor is not responsible for detecting noncompliance but must be alert to information suggesting noncompliance. When noncompliance identified: (1) Understand the nature, (2) Evaluate financial statement impact, (3) Discuss with management/governance, (4) Consider legal advice, (5) Evaluate implications for the audit (reliability of management representations, fraud risk), (6) Consider reporting obligations (may have legal requirement to report, e.g., to regulators).",
