    explanation: "SSARS level of assurance hierarchy: (1) Preparation (AR-C §70): no assurance, no report. (2) Compilation (AR-C §80): no assurance, report issued. Independence NOT required. (3) Review (AR-C §90): limited assurance, report issued. Independence IS required. (4) Audit (AU-C §700): reasonable assurance, opinion issued. Independence IS required. Key differences: Reviews require inquiry and analytical procedures (substantive work). Compilations require only reading the financial statements for obvious errors and understanding the client's industry. Reviews are substantially more costly/time-consuming than compilations but less than audits.",
