      1: "Why option B is WRONG - Compilations generally take *less* time than reviews. Reviews involve more procedures, such as inquiries and analytical procedures, making them more time-consuming.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Compilations require *less* testing than reviews. Compilations primarily involve presenting financial information in the proper format, while reviews require some substantive procedures.",
