    correctAnswer: 3,
    explanation: "AICPA ET §1.510 (Contingent Fees): Prohibited for attest clients: (1) Preparing original/amended tax returns, (2) Performing audit, review, or compilation, (3) Any service where the CPA also performs an attest engagement. Contingent fee = fee where no fee is charged unless a specified result is attained (or the amount of the fee depends on the specified result). Permitted: (1) Contingent fees for non-attest clients (consulting, M&A advisory), (2) Tax representation: IRS examination, refund claims for attest clients (result determines the fee amount) — generally allowed. The prohibition ensures the CPA's objectivity is not compromised by a financial stake in the outcome.",
