    correctAnswer: 3,
    explanation: "AU-C §500 — Types of audit procedures: (1) Inspection — examining records, documents, or physical assets, (2) Observation — watching a process or procedure being performed, (3) Inquiry — seeking information from knowledgeable persons (oral or written), (4) Confirmation — obtaining direct written response from a third party, (5) Recalculation — checking mathematical accuracy (footing, extensions, depreciation calculations), (6) Reperformance — independently re-executing a procedure or control (e.g., re-performing a bank reconciliation), (7) Analytical procedures — evaluating financial data through analysis of plausible relationships. Each provides different levels of reliability and addresses different assertions.",
