    educational: "Changes in accounting principles are permitted when the new principle is preferable and the change is accounted for in accordance with GAAP. To maintain comparability, auditors must highlight these changes, even when justified, to ensure users understand the impact on the financial statements. This is achieved through an emphasis-of-matter paragraph, which doesn't affect the overall 'clean' opinion.",
    examTip: "On the exam, remember that 'justified accounting change + proper disclosure' usually leads to an unmodified opinion with an emphasis-of-matter paragraph, not a modified opinion.",
    memoryAid: "GAAP Change = Good Opinion + Emphasis",
