      1: "Why option B is WRONG - ISAs are not exclusively for non-public companies. While US GAAS issued by the ASB primarily applies to non-issuers, ISAs can be used for both public and non-public entities globally.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - While US GAAS is converging with ISAs, they are not identical. Significant differences exist in terminology, reporting requirements, and the level of detail provided in the standards.",
      3: "Why option D is CORRECT - ISAs, issued by the IAASB, differ from US GAAS (issued by the ASB) in several key areas. These include the use of different terminology like \"Key Audit Matters\" versus \"Critical Audit Matters\" (used by the PCAOB for public companies), different going concern requirements where ISAs require an explicit statement, and the issuing body itself.",
