      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Financial statements intended for general public use require a general-use report, not a restricted-use report, as the information is meant to be accessible to a broad audience.",
      3: "Why option D is CORRECT - Restricted-use reports are specifically designed for situations where the information is relevant only to identified parties, such as when using a special purpose framework required by a regulator or contract.",
