    explanation: "Under AU-C 501.04, when inventory is material, the auditor should: (1) ATTEND the physical inventory counting to: (a) evaluate management's instructions and procedures, (b) OBSERVE the performance of management's count procedures, (c) INSPECT the inventory, and (d) perform TEST COUNTS. (2) Perform procedures over the entity's final inventory records to determine whether they accurately reflect the actual count. If attendance at the count is IMPRACTICABLE (e.g., inventory at remote locations), the auditor performs alternative procedures or considers the effect on the opinion. If the entity uses perpetual inventory records, the auditor also evaluates whether those records are reliable. The count date need not be the year-end date if controls over inventory movements between the count date and year-end are tested.",
