    question: "Under AU-C 610, when the external auditor uses the work of internal auditors, the external auditor:",
    options: ["Can outsource all testing to internal audit","Must evaluate internal audit's competence, objectivity, and systematic/disciplined approach, and then REPERFORM some of the work to evaluate its adequacy","Accepts internal audit's conclusions without review","Must perform all procedures independently without using internal audit"],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Under AU-C 610.07-.09, the external auditor may use internal auditors' work but must: (1) Evaluate the internal audit function's: COMPETENCE (qualifications, training), OBJECTIVITY (reporting structure, freedom from conflicting responsibilities), and APPLICATION OF A SYSTEMATIC AND DISCIPLINED APPROACH (quality control, documentation). (2) Evaluate the ADEQUACY of specific internal audit work for the external audit's purposes — including REPERFORMING some of the work. (3) Not use internal audit to perform procedures in areas of: significant judgment, higher risk of material misstatement, or where the external auditor's own procedures are needed. The external auditor remains SOLELY RESPONSIBLE for the audit opinion. Internal auditors may also provide DIRECT ASSISTANCE under specific circumstances (AU-C 610.24).",
