      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - AU-C 610 explicitly requires the external auditor to direct, supervise, and review the work of internal auditors providing direct assistance. Obtaining written acknowledgment of confidentiality and evaluating objectivity threats are also mandatory steps to ensure the integrity of the audit process. The external auditor retains ultimate responsibility for the audit opinion.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Direct assistance, by definition, involves the external auditor's direction and oversight; internal auditors cannot work independently in this context. Lack of oversight would violate auditing standards and compromise the reliability of the audit evidence.",
