    explanation: "AU-C 620.09 through 12 requires the auditor to: (1) evaluate the specialist's competence (qualifications, experience, certifications), capabilities (ability to perform the specific work), and objectivity (freedom from conflicts of interest, relationship with the client); (2) obtain an understanding of the specialist's field sufficient to determine the nature, scope, and objectives of the work; (3) agree on the terms (nature, objectives, assumptions, methods); (4) evaluate the adequacy of the specialist's work (methods used, assumptions, findings, consistency with other evidence). The auditor cannot delegate audit responsibility — the audit opinion remains solely the auditor's. The specialist is not ordinarily referenced in an unmodified opinion.",
