    educational: "Before accepting an audit engagement, auditors perform preliminary procedures to evaluate the engagement's feasibility. These procedures focus on the firm's ability to perform the audit ethically and competently, and on the client's integrity. The goal is to identify any red flags early on that might make the engagement too risky or unsuitable.",
    examTip: "Remember the pre-engagement phase focuses on evaluating the *acceptability* of the engagement, not performing audit procedures.",
