    examTip: "When evaluating materiality, always consider the perspective of a reasonable investor or creditor using the financial statements to make decisions.",
    memoryAid: "Think 'I.M.P.A.C.T.' - Influence on users' decisions, Magnitude, Perspective of a reasonable person, All facts and circumstances, Cumulative effect, Threshold (no fixed one).",
