    educational: "The monitoring component of internal control is crucial for ensuring that the other components are functioning effectively over time. It's about proactively identifying and addressing weaknesses in the system of internal control, not just reacting to problems after they occur. Effective monitoring helps an organization adapt to changing circumstances and maintain reliable financial reporting.",
    examTip: "When a question mentions 'monitoring,' think about the ongoing and periodic nature of the process, and the importance of reporting deficiencies.",
