      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Confirming inventory quantities with third-party warehouses primarily addresses existence and rights (ownership), not the valuation of that inventory.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Tracing inventory items to shipping documents primarily tests the completeness of sales and cutoff, ensuring that goods shipped are properly recorded as sales and removed from inventory.",
