      1: "Why option B is WRONG - If tolerable misstatement increases, you can accept a larger range of potential errors, thus requiring a smaller sample size.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Accepting sampling risk means you are willing to tolerate the possibility that your sample doesn't accurately reflect the population, which would actually decrease the required sample size.",
