      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - Effective IT General Controls (ITGCs) ensure that changes to automated application controls are properly authorized, tested, and implemented, and that access to the controls is restricted. This reduces the risk of unauthorized modifications, allowing auditors to rely on the controls with less frequent retesting.",
