    educational: "SQMS No. 1 shifts the focus from quality control to quality management, emphasizing a proactive and risk-based approach. Firms must establish quality objectives, identify risks to achieving those objectives, and design responses to mitigate those risks. This continuous process ensures the firm consistently delivers high-quality engagements.",
    examTip: "When a question mentions SQMS No. 1, immediately think 'risk-based' and look for answers that involve identifying, assessing, and responding to risks.",
