    educational: "Auditors must understand the client's business, industry, and internal controls to effectively assess the risk of material misstatement in the financial statements. This understanding allows auditors to tailor their audit procedures to address specific risks, ensuring a higher quality audit. Without this understanding, the auditor risks missing critical areas of potential misstatement.",
    examTip: "Always remember that risk assessment is the foundation of the audit process; understanding the entity is the first step in identifying those risks.",
    memoryAid: "I-R-A: Understand the Industry, Risks, and Audit approach.",
