    educational: "Financial forecasts and projections are prospective financial statements, but they serve different purposes. Forecasts aim to predict the most likely outcome based on current expectations, while projections explore hypothetical scenarios. Understanding this distinction is crucial for interpreting and using these statements effectively.",
