    educational: "Attribute sampling is used when auditors need to evaluate the effectiveness of internal controls. It helps determine how often a control is not operating as intended, providing evidence about the reliability of the control environment. The auditor is interested in the rate of deviation from the prescribed control.",
    examTip: "Remember that attribute sampling is for tests of controls (yes/no: did the control operate?), while variables sampling is for substantive testing (how much: what is the dollar value?).",
    memoryAid: "A-T-T-R-I-B-U-T-E: A Test To Rate Internal control Behavior Using Tests of controls to Estimate deviation rate.",
    reference: "AU-C 530.A7",
