    question: "During the audit of Stellar Corporation, you observe that the CEO consistently overrides established internal controls related to revenue recognition when quarterly earnings targets are at risk of not being met. The CFO, while aware of these overrides, does not challenge the CEO's actions, citing the CEO's 'superior knowledge of the business.' The audit committee, though comprised of independent directors, has not questioned these actions, primarily due to their perceived lack of expertise in accounting matters and a deference to management's judgment. According to AU-C 315, considering the components of internal control, which of the following is most significantly compromised in this scenario?",
    options: ["Control Environment","Risk Assessment","Control Activities","Monitoring Activities"],
