    difficulty: "easy",
    skillLevel: "Analysis",
    question: "An auditor is performing analytical procedures in the planning stage of an audit. Which of the following relationships would be the LEAST useful in identifying potential risks of material misstatement?",
    options: ["Comparing the current year's sales revenue to the prior year's sales revenue and budget.","Comparing the current year's inventory turnover rate to the industry average.","Comparing the current year's net income to the current year's cash flow from operations.","Comparing the current year's depreciation expense to the prior year's depreciation expense without considering any changes in asset base."],
    correctAnswer: 3,
