    difficulty: "medium",
    skillLevel: "Application",
    question: "ABC & Co., a CPA firm with 10 partners and 40 professional staff, performs audits of several publicly traded companies. During its ongoing monitoring activities, the firm's quality management team identified a significant deficiency in the firm's documentation of audit procedures related to revenue recognition for one of its largest clients. According to SQMS 1, what is ABC & Co.'s most appropriate course of action?",
    options: ["Immediately withdraw from the audit engagement with the client to avoid potential legal liability.","Communicate the deficiency to the engagement partner and require them to develop and implement a remedial action plan, including additional training for the audit team, and then monitor the effectiveness of the remedial actions.","Inform the PCAOB of the deficiency within 30 days of its discovery, as it relates to audits of public companies.","Increase the scope of the next peer review to specifically address the identified deficiency in revenue recognition documentation."],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "According to SQMS 1, when a significant deficiency is identified, the firm should communicate the deficiency to the appropriate individuals (in this case, the engagement partner) and take appropriate remedial actions. The firm should then monitor the effectiveness of those actions. This aligns with the principle of continuous improvement embedded in SQMS 1.",
