    question: "ABC CPA firm is considering accepting a new audit engagement for XYZ Corp, a publicly traded company in the biotechnology industry. ABC has limited experience auditing biotechnology companies, but the partner in charge believes they can quickly learn the industry. Before accepting the engagement, which of the following factors is MOST important for ABC CPA firm to consider?",
    options: ["Whether the engagement fee offered by XYZ Corp is sufficiently high to justify the learning curve.","Whether ABC has access to individuals with suitable competence to perform the engagement, which may be achieved through training or the use of specialists.","Whether XYZ Corp has a strong internal audit function that can compensate for ABC's lack of industry experience.","Whether XYZ Corp is willing to provide ABC with access to its competitors' financial statements for benchmarking purposes."],
