    question: "XYZ & Co., a CPA firm, has implemented a system of quality management in accordance with SQMS 1. As part of its monitoring activities, the firm identified a significant deficiency related to the engagement performance component. Specifically, engagement documentation consistently lacked evidence of partner review on high-risk audits, potentially impacting audit quality. According to SQMS 1, which of the following actions is MOST appropriate for XYZ & Co. to take?",
    options: ["Immediately report the deficiency to the AICPA Peer Review Program and cease performing high-risk audits until the deficiency is resolved.","Design and implement a remediation plan to address the deficiency, evaluate the effectiveness of the remediation, and communicate the deficiency and remediation to relevant personnel.","Document the deficiency in the firm's internal quality control manual and conduct a root cause analysis within the next fiscal year.","Increase the frequency of pre-issuance reviews on all audit engagements to compensate for the lack of partner review on high-risk audits."],
