    options: ["Jupiter Corp. is under investigation by the SEC for potentially inflating its earnings through aggressive revenue recognition practices. This investigation commenced shortly before year-end.","Jupiter Corp. recently implemented a new enterprise resource planning (ERP) system. The system went live six months before year-end, and some initial data migration issues were noted but subsequently resolved.","Jupiter Corp. is a publicly traded company with a complex ownership structure. The audit team has audited Jupiter Corp. for the past 5 years with no significant issues identified.","Jupiter Corp. has a small internal audit function that reports to the CFO and has a limited scope of responsibilities."],
