    question: "During the planning stage of an audit, an auditor determined a preliminary materiality threshold of $500,000 based on 5% of normalized income before taxes. Subsequently, the auditor discovered that the company is close to violating a key debt covenant related to its current ratio. Which of the following statements is most accurate regarding the impact of this discovery on materiality?",
    options: ["The materiality threshold should be increased to reduce the risk of failing to detect a material misstatement.","The materiality threshold should remain unchanged as it was appropriately determined based on income before taxes.","The materiality threshold should be decreased because the violation of a debt covenant would likely be considered a qualitatively material misstatement, even if quantitatively small.","The auditor should withdraw from the engagement as the debt covenant violation creates an unacceptable level of risk."],
