    options: ["The auditor should only inquire about fraud risks if there is a reason to believe that fraud may be present.","The auditor should inquire about management's process for identifying and responding to the risks of fraud, and their communication to those charged with governance.","The auditor is only required to inquire of senior management and the audit committee regarding fraud.","The auditor should primarily focus on specific instances of fraud that have already been detected within the organization."],
