    options: ["$2.5 million, based on 0.5% of revenue, due to the company's consistent profitability.","$4 million, based on 1% of total assets, due to the volatile industry.","$2.5 million, based on 5% of net income before tax, because this is the most conservative approach.","$5 million, based on 1% of revenue, as this is the most commonly used benchmark."],
    correctAnswer: 1,
