    options: ["Yes, because the spouse's and dependent child's ownership are not material to your personal financial situation.","No, because the combined ownership of Beta Corp. stock by you and your immediate family creates a covered member impairment to independence.","Yes, because the stock was acquired through a brokerage account, which constitutes indirect ownership.","No, because any ownership of a client's stock by a covered member's immediate family automatically impairs independence, regardless of materiality."],
