    subtopic: "Monitoring and Remediation Process",
    difficulty: "hard",
    skillLevel: "Analysis",
    question: "ABC & Co., a CPA firm, has established a system of quality management in accordance with SQMS 1. As part of its monitoring activities, the firm identified a significant deficiency related to partner consultation on high-risk engagements. Specifically, the firm discovered that partners were not consistently documenting their consultations, hindering the firm's ability to demonstrate compliance with its consultation policy. Which of the following actions would be MOST appropriate for ABC & Co. to take as part of its remediation process to address this deficiency?",
    options: ["A. Revise the firm's risk assessment to increase the likelihood of the deficiency recurring, thereby prompting more frequent monitoring.","B. Implement a policy requiring mandatory external peer review of all high-risk engagements to compensate for the lack of documented internal consultations.","C. Evaluate the severity and pervasiveness of the deficiency, communicate the deficiency to those responsible for taking corrective action, and implement a revised consultation documentation process with training.","D. Disclose the deficiency in the firm's report on its system of quality management and rely on regulators to identify appropriate corrective actions."],
    correctAnswer: 2,
