    question: "During the client acceptance process for auditing Johnson Co., the audit firm of Miller & Zois discovered that several former employees of Johnson Co. had filed complaints with the Department of Labor alleging wage theft and unsafe working conditions. These allegations occurred during the tenure of the current CEO. Which of the following actions should Miller & Zois take *FIRST* in response to this information?",
    options: ["Discuss the allegations with Johnson Co.'s audit committee to assess the CEO's response and any internal investigations conducted.","Decline the engagement due to the potential impact on the audit firm's reputation.","Immediately report the allegations to the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (PCAOB).","Request Johnson Co.'s legal counsel to provide an opinion on the validity of the allegations."],
