    question: "During the audit of Apex Manufacturing, the auditor, Sarah, is testing the effectiveness of Apex's controls over the authorization of credit sales. Apex processes approximately 5,000 credit sales transactions per month. Sarah has determined that a deviation rate of 3% would indicate that the controls are not operating effectively. She decides to use statistical sampling. Which of the following sample sizes would be most appropriate for Sarah to use in her tests of controls, assuming she desires a 90% confidence level and an expected deviation rate of 1%?",
