    question: "An auditor is using attributes sampling to test the effectiveness of a company's internal controls over sales invoices. The auditor has defined a tolerable deviation rate of 5% and expects the actual deviation rate to be approximately 2%. Which of the following statements is most accurate regarding the determination of the sample size?",
    options: ["The sample size should be larger if the auditor uses statistical sampling because it requires a more precise calculation.","The sample size will be smaller if the auditor uses statistical sampling because it allows for a quantified level of risk.","The sample size will be the same whether the auditor uses statistical or non-statistical sampling because the tolerable deviation rate and expected deviation rate are the same.","The auditor can only use statistical sampling if the population size is known."],
    correctAnswer: 1,
