    options: ["Must disclaim an opinion on the financial statements due to the inability to observe the inventory count.","May observe a subsequent physical inventory count and apply appropriate tests of intervening transactions.","May review the client's perpetual inventory records and apply gross profit tests to ascertain the reasonableness of the year-end inventory balance.","Are required to perform alternative procedures, such as vouching all purchases and sales transactions for the year, to ensure the inventory balance is fairly stated."],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "When the auditor is unable to observe the count of the entity's inventory at year-end, the auditor should attend a subsequent physical inventory count, and perform roll-back procedures to test the intervening transactions from the subsequent count date back to year-end (AU-C 501.A15).",
