    options: ["Confirmations are required to be used for all audits of financial statements under generally accepted auditing standards.","The auditor should consider confirming accounts receivable when the combined assessed level of inherent and control risk is low and substantive analytical procedures provide sufficient appropriate audit evidence.","Confirmation of accounts receivable is required if the accounts receivable balance is material.","There is a presumption that the auditor will confirm accounts receivable unless they are immaterial, confirmations are expected to be ineffective, or the combined assessed level of inherent and control risk is low and substantive analytical procedures provide sufficient appropriate audit evidence."],
