    options: ["Obtain written representations from management that the transaction was conducted at arm's length and that the terms were comparable to those that would have been obtained in a transaction with an unrelated party.","Determine whether the transaction was properly authorized and approved by the board of directors and review the minutes of the board meeting where the transaction was discussed.","Confirm the details of the transaction, including the sales price and terms, directly with the CEO's brother-in-law.","Disclose the transaction in the auditor's report as a material weakness in internal control, regardless of whether the transaction is fairly presented in the financial statements."],
