    question: "During the audit of Stellar Corp., the auditor identified a heightened risk of material misstatement related to revenue recognition due to aggressive sales targets set by management. As part of the audit procedures, the auditor decided to perform accounts receivable confirmation. Stellar Corp. has 5,000 customer accounts, with the top 100 accounts representing 75% of the total accounts receivable balance. The auditor decides to use a non-statistical sampling approach. Which of the following would be the MOST effective approach for selecting accounts for confirmation to address the heightened risk of material misstatement?",
    options: ["Select a random sample of 100 accounts from the entire population of 5,000 accounts to ensure broad coverage.","Stratify the population into two groups: the top 100 accounts and the remaining 4,900 accounts. Select all of the top 100 accounts and a random sample of 50 accounts from the remaining 4,900 accounts.","Select only the top 50 accounts with the largest outstanding balances and confirm these accounts.","Select a sample of 100 accounts based on their credit ratings, focusing on those with the lowest ratings."],
    correctAnswer: 1,
