    question: "During the audit of Johnson Co., the auditor identified a material weakness in the company's IT general controls related to user access. Specifically, terminated employees' access to the accounting system is not always promptly removed. The auditor assessed control risk as high for several assertions related to revenue recognition and wants to perform tests of controls to potentially reduce the assessed level of control risk. Which of the following procedures would be the MOST effective test of controls to address this specific weakness?",
    options: ["Perform a walkthrough of the revenue recognition process, tracing a sample of transactions from initiation to recording in the financial statements.","Examine the personnel termination records for the period under audit and compare them to the user access logs of the accounting system to identify any terminated employees who still have active access.","Select a sample of revenue transactions and vouch them to supporting documentation, such as sales orders and shipping documents.","Review the company's documented policies and procedures related to user access and interview IT personnel about their understanding of the policies."],
