    question: "You are auditing the financial statements of Apex Manufacturing, Inc. for the year ended December 31, 2023. Apex's accounts receivable balance at year-end is $2,500,000. Based on your risk assessment, you've determined that the risk of material misstatement related to accounts receivable is high. You've decided to use accounts receivable confirmation as a substantive procedure. Apex has 1,000 customers. Which of the following courses of action would be MOST appropriate regarding the type and timing of confirmation requests?",
    options: ["Send positive confirmation requests to all 1,000 customers as of December 31, 2023.","Send negative confirmation requests to a sample of 200 customers with large balances as of December 31, 2023.","Send positive confirmation requests to a sample of 200 customers with large balances as of December 31, 2023 and perform alternative procedures for non-responses.","Send negative confirmation requests to all 1,000 customers as of November 30, 2023, and perform roll-forward procedures to December 31, 2023."],
