    explanation: "When the risk of material misstatement is high, positive confirmations are generally preferred (AU-C 505.08). Positive confirmations require customers to respond, indicating whether they agree or disagree with the balance. Selecting a sample of large balances focuses on areas where misstatements are more likely to be material. Performing alternative procedures for non-responses is essential to obtain sufficient appropriate audit evidence (AU-C 330.20).",
