    question: "Which of the following statements is most accurate regarding the scope and limitations of management representations obtained during an audit?",
    options: ["Management representations are a substitute for other audit procedures and provide sufficient appropriate audit evidence to support the auditor's opinion.","Management representations are primarily used to corroborate information obtained through other audit procedures and should not be the sole basis for an audit opinion.","Management representations are optional and are only required if the auditor suspects management fraud.","Management representations are only relevant for material items and are not required for immaterial items."],
