    explanation: "Analytical procedures performed during the planning stage are used to identify unusual fluctuations and relationships that may indicate areas of higher risk. These areas will then require more detailed testing during the audit. AU-C 520.5 states that analytical procedures should be applied to assist the auditor in planning the nature, timing, and extent of other auditing procedures.",
