      0: "Obtaining cutoff information is crucial to ensure that inventory is recorded in the correct accounting period. The auditor needs to determine the last shipping and receiving document numbers to verify proper cutoff (AU-C 500).",
      1: "Performing test counts allows the auditor to verify the accuracy of the client's count and identify any discrepancies (AU-C 530).",
      2: "Evaluating management's procedures is essential to assess the reliability of the inventory count. The auditor needs to determine if the count is being performed accurately and consistently (AU-C 500).",
