    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "The fire is a Type II subsequent event (condition did not exist at the balance sheet date). Type II subsequent events require disclosure in the notes to the financial statements, but do not require adjustment of the financial statements. (AU-C 560.06 and .10)",
