    options: ["Statistical sampling requires the auditor to use judgment in determining sample size, while non-statistical sampling does not.","Statistical sampling allows the auditor to quantify the sampling risk, while non-statistical sampling does not.","Non-statistical sampling is more appropriate when testing controls, while statistical sampling is better for substantive procedures.","Non-statistical sampling eliminates the need for the auditor to document the sampling plan."],
