      0: "A is incorrect because while increasing the sample size for testing accounts payable controls is relevant, reducing substantive testing of revenue is inappropriate given the indications of potential revenue recognition fraud. A response to fraud risk needs to be targeted and specific.",
      2: "C is incorrect because relying on existing internal controls and reducing the overall scope of the audit is inappropriate when material weaknesses have been identified. The audit should be responsive to the assessed risks of material misstatement due to fraud (AU-C 240).",
      3: "D is incorrect because focusing primarily on testing controls over accounts payable, while important, neglects the heightened risk of revenue recognition fraud. A comprehensive approach is required when multiple fraud risks are present.",
