    topic: "Risk assessment procedures",
    subtopic: "Understanding the Entity and Its Environment",
    difficulty: "medium",
    skillLevel: "Application",
    question: "During the planning phase of an audit, an auditor is assessing inherent risk related to inventory. The company, a manufacturer of custom furniture, recently implemented a new, complex Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) system. The system is designed to track raw materials, work-in-process, and finished goods inventory in real-time. However, several employees have expressed difficulty using the new system, and the auditor observes a backlog of unprocessed transactions related to inventory movements. Which of the following procedures would be MOST appropriate for the auditor to perform as part of risk assessment related to inventory?",
    options: ["Perform a detailed substantive test of inventory balances at year-end to detect material misstatements.","Increase the reliance on internal controls related to inventory and reduce the extent of substantive testing.","Conduct walkthroughs of the inventory cycle, focusing on how transactions are processed through the new ERP system, and interview employees to understand system-related challenges.","Issue a management letter immediately, highlighting the weaknesses in the ERP system and recommending a complete system overhaul."],
