    difficulty: "medium",
    skillLevel: "Analysis",
    question: "During the planning stage of an audit, an auditor is identifying risks of material misstatement related to regulatory matters affecting the client, a publicly traded manufacturing company. Which of the following regulatory factors would most likely indicate a heightened risk of material misstatement?",
    options: ["A significant increase in the number of environmental violation notices received by the client from the EPA in the past year, along with substantial fines.","The client's industry trade association has issued new voluntary guidelines for product safety testing.","The client has recently implemented a new enterprise resource planning (ERP) system.","The client made a routine change in its inventory valuation method from FIFO to weighted-average."],
    correctAnswer: 0,
