    question: "During the audit of Johnson Manufacturing, the auditor identified that the company's purchasing department routinely approves invoices exceeding $10,000 without obtaining three competitive bids. The company's stated policy requires three competitive bids for all purchases exceeding $10,000. The purchasing manager stated that due to time constraints, this policy is often bypassed, especially during peak production periods. Which of the following internal control components is most directly affected by this exception?",
    options: ["Control Activities","Risk Assessment","Monitoring Activities","Control Environment"],
