    explanation: "The correct answer is Control Activities. Control activities are the actions established by policies and procedures to help ensure that management's directives to mitigate risks to the achievement of objectives are carried out. Requiring three competitive bids for purchases exceeding a certain threshold is a control activity designed to ensure fair pricing and prevent fraud. The bypass of this policy directly undermines the effectiveness of control activities. (AU-C 315.A124)",
