    question: "You are auditing Johnson Manufacturing, a publicly traded company. Preliminary net income before tax is $5,000,000 and total revenue is $50,000,000. Using a range of 0.5% - 1% of total revenue, and 5% - 10% of net income before tax, what is the range of preliminary materiality you should consider when planning the audit?",
