    correctAnswer: 2,
    explanation: "The correct answer is C. Materiality based on total revenue is calculated as 0.5% of $50,000,000 = $250,000 to 1% of $50,000,000 = $500,000. Materiality based on net income is calculated as 5% of $5,000,000 = $250,000 to 10% of $5,000,000 = $500,000. Because the auditor must consider multiple benchmarks, the auditor needs to consider the higher end of both ranges. Thus, the range is $500,000 (higher end of the revenue range) to $500,000 (higher end of the net income range). However, the auditor must also consider qualitative factors, and generally set materiality at a level lower than the maximum of the range. $500,000 to $1,000,000 is the most appropriate range.",
