    question: "Sarah is a senior manager at Miller & Zois CPA firm. She is assigned to the audit engagement for TechCorp, a publicly traded company. Sarah's spouse owns 500 shares of TechCorp stock, acquired through an inheritance, which represents less than 1% of TechCorp's outstanding shares and has a current market value of $10,000. Sarah does not participate in any of TechCorp's investment decisions. Which of the following statements is correct regarding Sarah's independence with respect to the TechCorp audit?",
    options: ["Sarah's independence is impaired because her spouse has a direct financial interest in TechCorp.","Sarah's independence is not impaired because the spouse's stock ownership is immaterial to the spouse's net worth.","Sarah's independence is impaired only if Sarah participates in the investment decisions related to the TechCorp stock.","Sarah's independence is not impaired because the stock was acquired through inheritance."],
