    question: "A CPA firm, Smith & Jones, is auditing a publicly traded company, Alpha Corp. A partner at Smith & Jones owns 500 shares of Alpha Corp. stock. While the partner does not work on the Alpha Corp. audit, the partner's ownership is known by all members of the firm. According to the AICPA Code of Professional Conduct, which of the following is the MOST appropriate course of action?",
    options: ["The partner must dispose of the Alpha Corp. stock to maintain independence.","As long as the partner does not work on the Alpha Corp. audit, the ownership is permissible.","The partner must disclose the stock ownership to Alpha Corp.'s management.","The partner must recuse themselves from any partnership decisions related to Alpha Corp."],
    correctAnswer: 0,
