    options: ["The audit firm can maintain independence as long as the spouse's stock ownership is disclosed to Acme Corp.'s audit committee.","The audit firm's independence is impaired unless the spouse disposes of the stock prior to the start of fieldwork.","The audit firm can maintain independence as long as the spouse does not participate in any audit-related decisions.","The audit firm's independence is impaired, but the firm can still issue an audit opinion if Acme Corp. provides a written waiver."],
    correctAnswer: 1,
