    skillLevel: "Analysis",
    question: "Which of the following is the MOST appropriate response when a CPA firm identifies a significant deficiency in its system of quality management?",
    options: ["Immediately report the deficiency to the PCAOB and cease performing any audit services.","Design and implement a remediation plan that addresses the root cause of the deficiency within a reasonable period.","Disclose the deficiency in the firm's next peer review report without taking any immediate corrective action.","Notify all current clients of the deficiency and allow them to decide whether to continue using the firm's services."],
